## Security Guidelines

Avid allows you to install an endpoint detection and response solution on your Newsroom Management system. This applies to both single-server and cluster environments. While Avid does not support any specific solution, you can find general guidelines and information related to CrowdStrike Falcon on the following Avid Knowledge Base page:

https://kb.avid.com/articles/en_US/troubleshooting/en239659

---

## Compatibility Notes and Issues

### Workstation & Server Compatibility Chart

Older client versions may log in to servers of the same or newer versions.  
Newer client versions cannot log in to servers with older versions.

| Client \ Server | MCNM 2023.7.x | 2024.10.x |
|-----------------|---------------|-----------|
| 2023.7.x | A | A |
| 2024.10.x | NA | A |

**A = Allowed | NA = Not Allowed**

---

### Qualified Operating Systems

**Newsroom Management Server**  
Ubuntu 22.04 LTS only.

Avid recommends keeping servers updated with the latest patches.

**iNEWS Workstation**  
Compatible with Windows 10 and Windows 11 only.

Chromium Embedded Framework version 116.

---

## Install and Upgrade Notes and Issues

### Upgrading to 2024.10.6

Client update only.  
Standard upgrade from 2024.10 or later.

Before upgrade:
Insert new client version `10.2.1.4` into `SYSTEM.CLIENT.VERSIONS`.

---

### Downgrade Notes and Issues

- Downgrading from 2024.10 requires restoring isam and database from backup.
- Downgrading to 2023.3 from 2023.7 is standard.
- Downgrading to 2022.12 or earlier is not supported without full reinstall.

---

## New Features in MediaCentral | Newsroom Management 2024.10.5

### On the Newsroom Management Server

- Configuration files loaded by services no longer require `maketab` or `makemontab`
- Windows Server 2025 support added

### On the iNEWS Workstation

- Dynamic Theme Change (no restart required)
- High Resolution Display / Sizing improvements
- Vector icon support
- Resizable dialogs
- Dockable main menu

---

## New Features in MediaCentral | Newsroom Management 2024.10.4

### Server

- Notify Server Kafka integration
- Improved CTMS data model

### Workstation

- Clear Channel option in MOS-MAP
- Improved key mapping for macros

---

## New Features in MediaCentral | Newsroom Management 2024.10

- Cloud UX wire notifications
- Secure Kafka connection
- Light & Dark themes
- Updated Chromium framework
- IDP support (Okta, KeyCloak)
- New browser shortcuts
- Enhanced certificate validation

---

## Fixed in Version 2024.10.6

Resolved:

- IN-180861 (macro recursion handling)
- IN-180872 (Print dialog crash with scaling)
- IN-180873 / IN-180887 (scroll jump issue)
- IN-180885 (GDI resource management improvements)

---

## Fixed in Version 2024.10.5

Multiple macro, crash, plugin, mailserver, RXNET, Unicode, UAC and DPI fixes.

---

## Fixed in Version 2024.10.4

Server stability improvements  
Wire server initialization updates  
Plugin drag-and-drop parsing fixes  
Database restore corrections

